		<title>Chinese Manufacturing Figures Can Test Market Strength</title>
		<link>https://www.atfx.com/en/analysis/market-news/chinese-manufacturing-figures-test-market-strength</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ATFX]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Sun, 26 Jan 2025 20:06:18 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Market news & Insights]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[China 50]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Recent news]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.atfx.com/?p=45342</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[Manufacturing figures from China on Monday can test the strength of the stock market. CHI50 – Weekly Chart The price of CHI50 has failed to get above the downtrend support and that level is vital for Monday’s data release. Chinese NBS manufacturing is released at 9:30am HKT with market watchers expecting a reading of 50.1. [&#8230;]]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Manufacturing figures from China on Monday can test the strength of the stock market.</span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-45343" src="https://www.atfx.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/CHI50-–-Weekly-Chart.png" alt="CHI50 – Weekly Chart" width="829" height="567" srcset="https://www.atfx.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/CHI50-–-Weekly-Chart.png 829w, https://www.atfx.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/CHI50-–-Weekly-Chart-300x205.png 300w, https://www.atfx.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/CHI50-–-Weekly-Chart-768x525.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 829px) 100vw, 829px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-weight: 400; font-size: 10pt;">CHI50 – Weekly Chart</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The price of </span><a href="https://www.atfx.com/en/markets/indices-trading" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span style="font-weight: 400;">CHI50</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> has failed to get above the downtrend support and that level is vital for Monday’s data release.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Chinese NBS manufacturing is released at 9:30am HKT with market watchers expecting a reading of 50.1. The 50 level is the difference between expansion and contraction and will be important for the market’s path this week.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Alongside the figures, investors are still wary of the coming actions on tariffs from Donald Trump. The new US President said he was considering a new 10% tariff on Chinese imports from as early as February 1. Trump also proposed new 25% tariffs on Mexico and Canada.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Beijing said last week that it was “firmly committed to safeguarding national interests”. China’s Foreign Ministry spokesperson Mao Ning added that, “there are no winners in a trade or a tariff war”.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">However, investors have been soothed by the early inaction from Trump on tariffs and he said that the two nations can have a “very good relationship” in the coming years.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">“China realizes that there&#8217;s an opportunity to negotiate with Trump,” said Liu Dongshu of the City University of Hong Kong. “And a better US-China relationship is more important to China than to the United States”.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Shanghai Composite is in need of a new boost after the 2024 stimulus rally faded. A manufacturing boost would help ahead of the Chinese New Year.</span></p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
